headline: 16-year-old killed after argument
formatted_address: Chestnut St & S Harrison St, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Ronald Kelson, who was featured in a local documentary about Wilmington crime violence as a teen poised to turn his life around, was shot after arguing with another man, police said. The man fired some 20 shots, including four that struck two homes.

Kelson was hit in the lower back, and the bullet severed the femoral artery that carries blood to the lower extremities, causing a heavy loss of blood. He was rushed to Christiana Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. On the night he was killed, there was a screening of the film at the Delaware Art Museum, but Kelson did not attend.                                                                  

The other victim was shot in the left elbow.

summary:

He was rushed to Christiana Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. At the time of the homicide, police said they did not know where Lee was shot and speculated he might have been driving himself to the hospital when he crashed.

More than a year later, Jeffery Kent was arrested and charged with first-degree murder and possession of a firearm during the commission of a felony in connection with Lee's death. He was committed to Howard R. Young Correctional Institution and was being held without bail.

headline: Three shot, one killed in Kosciusko Park

summary:
Tamekia Kearney, who lived in the 200 block of S. Franklin Street, was killed several blocks away in the center of Kosciusko Park, where police were summoned after residents heard at least three shots.

The other victims were a man found in the park near Kearney and a woman who was found conscious and alert in the 400 block of S. Connell St., which borders the park. Police released no other information about the crime or the victims and their injuries until announcing on July 3 that they arrested and charged Daiquan Reams for the murder and shootings.

In a statement, Attorney General Beau Biden and Wilmington Police Chief Michael Szczerba "applauded City residents who came forward with information ... emphasizing that the arrests and indictments occurred as a result of community input, along with the close work between the Wilmington Police and prosecutors, who routinely respond to the scene and work directly with police throughout investigations."

headline: Shootout at Eden Park soccer game leaves three dead

summary:

Curry's family told The News Journal that he was a potential witness for the state in its murder case against one of the suspects, Otis Phillips.

Spectators then opened fire on the gunmen, inciting a spray of bullets that left nearly 50 shell casings strewn around the field and parking lot. Curry died, along with Alexander Kamara, who was waiting to play his match, and suspect Sheldon Ogle, who drove the getaway car. Suspect Jeffery Phillips was struck in the leg, and a 33-year-old Baltimore man was hit in the shoulder.

Wilmington homicide detectives are investigating the slaying of a 32-year-old man from New Castle late Friday.

Cpl. Jamaine Crawford said city officers found the victim when responding to a report of shots fired at 10th and Bennett streets about 11:10 p.m.

Crawford did not release the name of the victim or other details, but reports at the scene indicated the victim was male.

The man was pronounced dead at the scene.

headline: Two shot, one fatally
formatted_address: Northeast Blvd & E 28th St, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary: Two people were shot near the Thunderguards Motorcycle Club Hall when a large crowd gathered at 28th Street and Northeast Boulevard. Kevin Bell, 30, of Wilmington, was shot to death and a 32-year-old woman was wounded.

headline: Man shot; two arrested after chase
formatted_address: 1000 Vandever Ave, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers responding to reports of shots fired learned a 20-year-old man was shot in the neck and taken to Wilmington Hospital via private vehicle.

Police learned that two suspects were possibly driving in a black Ford Crown Victoria in the Browntown area, and an officer spotted the car and tried to pull them over. The driver took off, though, and tried to get on I-95.

One suspect, Troy Dixon, got out of the moving car and discarded a black handgun before police caught him, officers said. The other suspect, Zaire Cephas, kept driving until his car was disabled and he took off on foot and hid in a marsh alongside the highway where police arrested him.

headline: Man shot multiple times
formatted_address: 800 N Clayton St, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Officers responding to reports of shots fired found a 30-year-old Wilmington man with multiple gunshot wounds.

No further details have been released.

headline: Pregnant woman shot in leg
formatted_address: 0 W 27th St, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers responding to reports of shots fired found a pregnant woman with a gunshot wound to her lower leg.

The woman told police she was standing on a nearby porch when she was struck. The investigation is ongoing.

headline: 29-year-old shot in lower body
formatted_address: 600 E 23rd St, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers were patrolling around 23rd and Pine streets when they heard gunfire. They found a 29-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his lower body.

The victim was unable to provide any suspect information, and his condition was not available.

headline: Man shot; two arrested after returning to scene
formatted_address: N West St & W 28th St, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers responding to reports of shots fired found a 19-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his arm.

Police learned that the victim was in a fight with the two suspects, Charlie Thompson and Andre Davis. Davis, police said, had a handgun that was fired during the fight. Both suspects then fled.

Thompson and Davis, though, returned to the scene later. Police tried to stop them, but the men ran and were arrested after a short foot chase. After the arrests, police also canvased the area and found a shotgun in the rear yard of a neighborhood daycare.

headline: Man shot in lower lip
formatted_address: 200 N Lombard St, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Officers responding to a report of shots fired found a man sitting in a car with a gunshot wound to his lower lip.

The victim told police he was sitting in the vehicle when a person came up to him and began firing. The man was able to get away and fled to a house nearby.

headline: Man dies after Christmas Eve shooting
formatted_address: 1203 West 2nd Street, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary: Myron J. Ashley, 29, of Wilmington, was allegedly shot and killed by Joshua Stephenson, 27, who is the brother of Ashley's girlfriend. She told police that Stephenson recently had stayed with them, but she had thrown him out about two weeks earlier because he was behaving erratically. She also said her brother has bi-polar disorder and schizophrenia and had not been taking his medication.

headline: Man shot fleeing from robbers
formatted_address: 900 East 23rd Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A Wilmington man suffered several gunshot wounds to his upper torso while attempting to flee from robbers.

Multiple subjects approached the man on East 23rd Street and tried to rob him. The victim ran and was shot but managed to make it to a nearby house where the resident called 911 on his behalf.

headline: Two New Castle men shot
formatted_address: 500 North Jefferson Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Officers responding to reports of shots fired found two victims, one with a single gunshot wound and the other with several wounds.

The suspect was described as a short male in his 20s with a beard and wearing a black hooded sweatshirt and black jeans. He was last seen running east through an alley in the 500 block of North Jefferson Street.

headline: Mid-afternoon shooting injures man
address: W. 25th Street and N. West Street

summary: Officers responding to reports of shots fired learned a a 23-year-old Wilmington man was shot multiple times and driven to Wilmington Hospital. No further information has been released.

headline: Fleeing man shot in calf
formatted_address: 2100 North West Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police were called to Wilmington Hospital after receiving a report that a 33-year-old shooting victim was at the hospital. The victim told police that he was walking in the 2100 block of North West Street when two men, both around 18 years old, approached him. While attempting to flee, the men shot at him and struck him in the calf.

One of the suspects was described as roughly 5'5" tall, 140 lbs, clean shaven and wearking a blue vest, black sweater and black knit hat. The second suspect was roughly 5'10" tall, 220-230 lbs, clean shaven and wearing a brown vest and black hooded sweatshirt.

headline: 15-year-old shot in leg
address: West 25th Street and North Tatnall Streets
formatted_address: Tatnall Street & West 25th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
After receiving reports of gunshots, Wilmington and Delaware State Police found a 15-year-old girl with a gunshot wound to her leg after.

The girl's parents were notified and she was taken to Wilmington Hospital. No further information has been released.

headline: 14-year-old shot over jacket
formatted_address: 800 East 23rd Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 14-year-old Wilmington boy was shot in the elbow after refusing to give his jacket to a robber.

The boy was walking through Speakman Park with a young woman when a boy, roughly 17-years-old, in dark clothing approached them and demanded that the victim give up his jacket. When the victim refused, the suspect pulled out a handgun and shot him in the elbow.

The suspect fled, and the victim ran to a home on North Locust Street where he contacted police.

headline: Man shot in buttocks
formatted_address: 400 West 30th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary: Police responding to reports of shooting found a 29-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his buttocks. The initial investigation revealed that an unknown man wearing a black hat and tan jacket approached the victim and began shooting. No further details have been made available.

headline: Woman shot during Trolley Square robbery
formatted_address: 1 Trolley Square, Wilmington, DE 19806
summary:
A female clerk at the Walgreens in Trolley Square was shot in the hip during an armed robbery.

Police said two men robbed the store of cash and pills from the pharmacy and shot the clerk as she was trying to flee the store. One suspect - described as wearing a black hooded sweatshirt, black pants, black mask and armed with a handgun - jumped over the checkout counter and took cash from the register. The second suspect - described as wearing a yellow puffy coat, navy blue running pants with vertical white stripes, a pink or purple mask and a large afro that was possibly a wig - raided the pharmacy.

The two men fled west through the parking lot.

headline: 16-year-old shot, killed
formatted_address: 0 East 24th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Ahkee Flonnory, 16, was shot and killed and a woman was wounded during a shooting.

Officers responding to a report of a shooting victim found Flonnory dead and lying on the ground. Later, police said a woman, whose age was not released, was also shot during the incident.

No further information has been released.

headline: Police officer shot in face
formatted_address: 1200 Peach Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Wilmington Police Officer Justin Wilkers was shot in the jaw while chasing a suspect in the Southbridge neighborhood.

Wilkers and his partner attempted to stop a vehicle for an equipment violation. The vehicle fled, though, and the officers began pursuit. When the vehicle stopped, several suspects fled on foot. As Wilkers was getting out of his car, one of the suspects drew a handgun and shot him in the jaw.

Two men, Ronald Boyce and Jared Wiggins, were arrested and police are looking for a third suspect.

headline: Man shot during burglary
formatted_address: 0 West 24th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police responding to reports of a shooting found a 29-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his chest.

Two men wearing all black and masks entered the victim's home and attempted to steal items. When the victim confronted the suspects, one of them shot him and fled southbound on North Tatnall Street.

headline: 53-year-old Townsend man shot, killed
formatted_address: 600 North Tatnall Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Police, responding to a call for shots fired, found Ioannis Kostikidis with a gunshot wound to his upper torso. The 53-year-old security guard for the American Beauty Academy was walking to his car when two men accosted him, then shot and killed him.

He was taken to Christiana Hospital where he died.

Police said the two men wore black hooded sweatshirts with the hoods pulled over their faces and were seen running from the scene, southbound on North Tatnall Street.

headline: 19-year-old shot on Fourth Street
formatted_address: 2300 West 4th Street, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Wilmington Police responded to St. Francis Hospital’s Emergency room in reference to a gunshot victim. The victim was driving on the 2300 block of West 4th Street when an unknown man, wearing dark clothing, began shooting at his car, striking the victim in his back.

The victim drove himself to St. Francis for treatment and was transported to Christiana Hospital by ambulance.

headline: Shooter opens fire at NCCo Courthouse
formatted_address: 500 North King Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Two women were shot to death when Thomas Matusiewicz opened fire at the New Castle County Courthouse.

The shooting began around 8 a.m., when Matusiewicz came to the courthouse with his son, David Matusiewicz, who had a child support hearing with victim Christine Belford. David Matusiewicz went through the security checkpoint, but Thomas Matusiewicz stayed and waited. When Belford arrived with her friend, Laura Mulford, Thomas Matusiewicz pulled out a .45-caliber handgun and shot and killed both Belford and Mulford.

Thomas Matusiewicz then shot two Capitol Police officers during a firefight before taking a bullet in the upper body and turning his gun on himself and committing suicide.

headline: 21-year-old shot multiple times

Police found the man with gunshot wounds to both legs when they arrived. The shooter was described as a young man between 6 feet and 6 feet 2 inches tall and between 240-250 pounds wearing a grey hooded sweatshirt. No descriptions were provided of the other four men.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

He was taken by ambulance to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in critical condition.

The victim was standing on the corner of 5th and Delamore streets when two men wearing masks began shooting at him and struck him in the back once before fleeing. After arriving at St. Francis, the victim was transported to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

The suspects were described as two men between 5 feet 10 inches and 6 feet tall with thin builds. On suspect was wearing a grey coat and armed with a handgun. The other was wearing a dark-colored, possibly with grey shoulders, and was armed with a rifle.

headline: Man killed inside Iggy's Food Market

summary:

No further information has been released.

The hospital contacted police when the teen arrived seeking treatment. The victim, though, was uncooperative.

Police said the man was sitting in a vehicle when an unknown suspect began firing at him from a dark-colored SUV. The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital, and police say he was uncooperative with the investigation.

No further information has been released.

summary:
A 25-year-old man was shot in the arm during an attempted robbery.

Police said four male suspects tried to rob the man. When the victim resisted, one of the suspects shot him.

The victim was taken by ambulance to Christiana Hospital where his condition was listed as stable.

summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting a shooting found a 21-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his stomach.

The victim was standing in the area of West 27th and Enterprise streets, police said, when an unknown man, described as roughly 6 feet tall and wearing all dark clothing, tried to rob him. When the victim refused to hand over property, the suspect shot him.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

headline: Man shot in buttocks
formatted_address: 900 Kirkwood Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting a shooting found a 30-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his buttocks.

The victim was walking in the area, police said, when a group of unknown suspects began shooting at him without provocation.

On April 1, Jerree Richardson, 21, of the 800 block of Bennett Street in Wilmington was arrested and charged in connection with the shooting.

headline: Three men wounded in morning shooting
formatted_address: 800 North Pine Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found two men with gunshot wounds.

A 21-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his abdomen was at the intersection of East 9th and North Pine streets. A 22-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his right leg was in a residence in the 1000 block of Pine Street.

A third victim, 25, was taken to Wilmington Hospital by private vehicle with gunshot wounds to his neck and torso. He was later transferred to Christiana Hospital and was listed in stable condition.

On April 3, Jerree Richardson, who was already in custody for the March 29 shooting of a 30-year-old Wilmington man, was charged in connection with the shootings after detectives were able to gather information that linked Richardson to a series of shootings that occurred in the city's east side neighborhood.

He was charged with two counts of first-degree attempted murder, first-degree assault, three counts of possession of a firearm during the commission of a felony, and possession of a deadly weapon during the commission of a felony.

headline: Bullet grazes 19-year-old's head
formatted_address: Vandever Avenue & Spruce Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found an unoccupied vehicle with the engine running and blood in the compartment area at the intersection of Vandever Avenue and Spruce Street.

Not long after, 19-year-old Kyref French arrived at Wilmington Hospital via private vehicle with a gunshot graze to his head.

French, a convicted felon and probationer, was later arrested after police found a firearm in the vehicle that transported him to the hospital. Detectives were able to link the handgun to French after executing a search warrant on his cell phone and finding pictures of him posing with the gun.

headline: Man shot after fight breaks out
formatted_address: 100 East 26th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting a large fight and shots fired found a 22-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his buttocks.

The victim was walking in the area, police said, when a large fight broke out. The victim heard gunshots and was struck in the buttocks.

Police responding to multiple calls for shots fired found a 19-year-old Wilmington man with a gunshot wound to his lower torso.

The victim was walking in the 1600 block of North Church Street when multiple gunshots were fired and the he was struck. He was taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Two men shot on 5th Street

Police responding to the scene after officers on patrol heard gunshots found a 39-year-old man with a gunshot graze wound to his right ear. He was taken to Wilmington Hospital and was listed in stable condition.

A second victim was taken to Wilmington Hospital via personal vehicle with a gunshot wound to his left thigh.

The men were walking in the are, police said, when they heard shots and realized they were hit.

Police were looking for a 16- to 18-year-old male with a grey hooded sweatshirt in connection with the shooting.

headline: Man injured in attempted shooting
formatted_address: 700 East 17th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call for shots fired found a 49-year-old man with minor lacerations to his left ear.

The man, police said, was sitting in a car and waiting for a friend when an unknown suspect began shooting. The shooter hit the car several times, causing glass to shatter and lacerate the victims ear. The victim was evaluated by EMS on the scene and refused transportation to the hospital.

One suspect was described as between 25 and 30 years old and wearing dark clothing and jeans. The second suspect was between 20 and 25 years old and wearing dark clothing and jeans.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

headline: Kid finds gun, shoots brother

summary:
An 11-year-old boy found a handgun and shot his 7-year-old brother in the hand, police said.

Wilmington police responded to the boys' home in reference to a shooting. The 11-year-old, police learned, found a handgun in the home and "unknowingly fired the weapon," striking his brother. No charges have been filed, according to a news release, and there was no mention of the boys' parents.

The boy was taken to A.I. DuPont Children's Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

headline: Man shot in arm

Police responded to a 911 call reporting shots fired. Several minutes later, an 18-year-old man showed up at Wilmington Hospital via private vehicle with a gunshot wound to his right arm.

No further information has been provided.

formatted_address: 1100 Read Street, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found a 40-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his right foot.

When police arrived, they found bloody footprints leading from Read Street to the victim in a house in the 1100 block of Pleasant Street. The victim was in his home on Read Street when a man, described as between 5'5" and 5'7", 130 lbs with a slight afro and black jeans, began firing into the house. The shooter was with a second male, and the two fled in an unknown direction.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

headline: Man shot in leg on 3rd Street
formatted_address: 1200 West 3rd Street, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting a shooting found a 25-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his left leg. The man was standing in the area when an unknown man shot him.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

Several days later, police arrested Shaquille Campbell in connection with the shooting. Campbell was charged with first-degree assault, possession of a deadly weapon during the commission of a felony and possession of a firearm by a person prohibited.

Campbell was taken into custody at the New Castle County Courthouse. He was at the courthouse for a court appearance for an unrelated charge for which he was out on bail.

headline: Two shot, one killed on Jefferson Street
formatted_address: 600 North Jefferson Street, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A 20-year-old Wilmington man was killed and a 22-year-old Philadelphia man was wounded during a shooting on Jefferson Street.

Police responding to a 911 call reporting a shooting found Toney Morgan in the street with multiple gunshot wounds. He was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was pronounced dead.

The Philadelphia man also suffered multiple gunshot wounds and was taken to Wilmington Hospital via private vehicle and was later transferred to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in critical condition.

Several days later, police said they arrested the Philadelphia man, Khalil Lewis, in connection with Morgan's death.

headline: Man shot on North Market

The man, police said, was walking the 2100 block of North Market Street when two unknown men began arguing. The victim said he heard gunfire and realized he was struck in the leg.

Police said the victim was walking in the area when he was struck by gunfire from unknown shooters.

headline: Man shot, killed on Claymont
formatted_address: 2600 North Claymont Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 27-year-old Wilmington man was shot and killed on North Claymont Street.

Officers responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found Marvin Moore with multiple gunshot wounds to his upper torso. he was taken to Christiana Hospital where he died.

A little more than two weeks later, members of the U.S. Marshals Service service arrested Darcell Coleman in East Orange, New Jersey in connection with the homicide. Once extradited to Delaware, Coleman will face charges of first-degree murder and possession of a firearm during the commission of a felony.

headline: Man shot in torso, arm

There are no suspects or motive known at this time, police wrote in a June 3 news release.

headline: Two store clerks shot, one killed

summary:
A Printz Convenience Store clerk was killed and another was injured during a shooting at the store.

Police responded to the store after receiving a 911 call reporting the shooting. There, they found Toney Berry, 29, and a 31-year-old man with multiple gunshot wounds. Both were taken to Christiana Hospital. Berry was pronounced dead at the hospital, and the other clerk was listed in critical condition.

Police said three men - one in his 20s, 6'2" and between 140 and 160 lbs; the second in his late teens, 5'7" and stocky; and the third short and stocky - entered the store, shot both clerks and fled. They were last seen running west on West 26th Street.

headline: Man shot on North West Street

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

The man was walking in the area of 23rd and Carter streets when he heard several gunshots, police said. The victim then ran to the 600 block of East 22nd Street when he realized he had been shot. The victim was uncooperative, police said, and did not provide any suspect information.

The man, who was intoxicated, heard gunshots in the area of 28th and North Washington Street. After realizing he had been shot, the man changed his pants and was taken to the hospital. He was uncooperative with police and did not provide any suspect information.

Police said the man was standing in the 700 block of East 22nd Street when he was shot by an unknown person. The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

One, a 35-year-old Wilmington man, had a gunshot wound to his right shin; and the other, a 31-year-old Wilmington man, had a gunshot wound to his buttocks/groin area.

Police said the shooting seems to have occurred near Taylor and North Bennett streets. Both men were transported to Christiana Hospital where they were each listed in stable condition.

headline: 19-year-old shot during attempted robbery

summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting a shooting found a 47-year-old woman with a gunshot wound to her buttocks and a 29-year-old woman with a gunshot wound to her thigh.

The two victims were sitting on a porch in the 600 block of West 6th Street when two unknown gunmen began firing at each other. The two women were caught in the crossfire and wounded, police said. Both victims were taken to Christiana Hospital where they were listed in stable condition.

One of the suspects, who was wearing a gray hooded sweatshirt, fled the scene in a silver two-door sedan.

headline: Teen shot, killed on North Van Buren Street
formatted_address: 2600 North Van Buren Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found 17-year-old Lamar Wilmer inside a residence with gunshot wounds to his upper body.

headline: Passenger in car shot on North Washington
formatted_address: North Washington Street & West 29th Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers on patrol heard gunfire in the area of West 29th and Washington streets but were unable to find a victim. Soon after, a 22-year-old Wilmington man arrived at Wilmington Hospital seeking treatment for a gunshot wound to his back.

Police said the victim was the right front passenger in a vehicle driving south on North Washington Street when an unknown gunman shot at the car multiple times.

Less than a month later, police arrested 20-year-old Devonte Lewis in connection with the shooting.

headline: Man shot walking on street
formatted_address: West 2nd Street & Delamore Place, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 19-year-old man was shot in Wilmington Thursday, raising to 152 the city’s record number of shooting victims this year.

A 911 call reported the shooting in the area of Second Street and Delamore Place, Cpl. Jamaine Crawford said.

Responding officers found the man, with a gunshot wound of an upper extremity, in the 1600 block of W. Fourth St., Crawford said.

headline: Christmas Day shooting

The shooting occurred when the man was walking in the unit block of East 25th Street. As the man neared the intersection with Lamotte Street, a person began shooting at him from a vehicle, Cpl. Jamaine Crawford, a Wilmington police spokesman.

After being shot, the man ran to the 100 block of East 24th Street and collapsed.

The victim was transported to Christiana Hospital by ambulance. Her condition is unknown.

An initial investigation suggests an unknown suspect entered the victim’s home and found her in her bedroom. The suspect shot the victim and fled in an unknown direction.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in stable condition.

headline: 16-year-old shot on 5th Street
formatted_address: 1500 West 5th Street, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police responding to a 911 call reporting shots fired found a 16-year-old boy inside a residence with a gunshot wound to his right leg.

The teen had bought marijuana in the area and was returning home when a thin man wearing a puffy black jacket approached and pulled a handgun. The gunman robbed the boy before shooting him in the leg.

The victim’s father, however, told The News Journal that his son's marijuana purchase had nothing to do with the shooting. He said his son was walking home from a friend’s house and was confronted by a group of kids looking for a boy that his son doesn't know. He said the group hit his son in the head with a gun, forced him to strip in the 12-degree weather, took his cellphone and told him to walk away before shooting him in the leg.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in serious but stable condition.

formatted_address: Elm and South Harrison Streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:

As officers tried first aid and CPR, a crowd of roughly 200 people formed and began throwing rocks at officers. Additional officers were called to provide security for EMS.

The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was pronounced dead.

Three men were indicted March 30, 2015. Jeffrey Clark, 26, and Rayshaun Johnson, 32, were arrested April 3, 2015, and charged with murder. Police continue to search for Christopher Harris.

headline: Man shot, killed at 24th and Market streets
formatted_address: 24th St & N Market St Wilmington DE 19802
summary:
A 46-year-old Wilmington man was shot and killed while fleeing from a group of young men intent on robbing him after a dice game, according to police and witnesses.

Witnesses on the corner of East 24th and Market streets said there was a dice game going on and Tracy Green was a player. Reportedly, Green heard the young men he was playing with say they were going to rob him, so he took his winnings and started to go when gunfire erupted, the residents said.

After he was critically wounded, Green continued to run from his assailants, then collapsed in the doorway of the Square Garden Chinese Restaurant at 2320 N. Market St. He was taken to Christiana Hospital where he died four hours later, said Wilmington Police Cpl. Mark Ivey.

One 18-year-old was hit in the leg, a 16-year-old was hit in the arm and the 21-year-old was shot in the buttocks. All three were hospitalized and should recover, police said.

The shooting punctuated a bloody weekend for Wilmington that saw seven injured by gun violence, six of those teenagers. The shootings killed two teens.

summary:
Markevis Clark, 32, was shot and killed late Saturday night, police said.

Investigators were called out to the 800 block of Vandever Ave. about 11:20 p.m. Saturday where they found Clark suffering from a gunshot wound to the head, police said.

He was taken to Wilmington Hospital where he died. 

Police said they were searching for 30-year-old Hakiem Anderson, in connection with Clark's homicide.

headline: Man shot in legs
formatted_address: 500 block of Vandever Ave., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 46-year-old man was shot in the legs early Tuesday, police said.

Police responded to the 500 block of Vandever Ave., about 2:15 a.m., for a shooting investigation and found the victim. 

He was treated at the scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Boy, 10, shot in head
formatted_address: 700 block of Townsend Place, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A 10-year-old boy was shot in the head early Tuesday in Southbridge, police said.

The boy was identified as Makhi Mitchell by family. 

The boy was shot at 1:50 a.m. Tuesday in the 700 block of Townsend Place, in the middle of a block of Wilmington Housing Authority row houses just west of South Heald Street. He was taken to Nemours/Alfred I. duPont Hospital for Children, where he was listed in critical condition.

A 24-year-old man has been charged with a weapons offense, but not the actual shooting.

headline: Man shot at Adams 4 Shopping Center
formatted_address: 200 block of N. Monroe St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A man was shot in the abdomen and one leg Wednesday afternoon, police said.

The shooting was reported at the Adams 4 Shopping Center shortly aft 4 p.m. Officers responding to the shopping center at Fourth and Adams streets learned that the 43-year-old victim had been taken by private vehicle to Wilmington Hospital before their arrival, police said.

Investigators determined he was shot in the 200 block of N. Monroe St., where evidence of the shooting was found, police said.

headline: Man shot in Hilltop area
formatted_address: 200 block of Delamore Place, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 22-year-old man was injured in a shooting in the city's Hilltop area, police said.

Officers were called at about 6:55 p.m. to the 200 block of Delamore Place for a report of a shooting. Upon arrival, a man was found with gunshot wounds to his thigh and hand, police said.

He was treated by New Castle County paramedics before he was taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Critically wounded victim arrives at hospital
formatted_address: Fifth and North Madison streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A man who was shot and critically wounded Tuesday was taken to Wilmington Hospital by private vehicle. 

A 911 call just after 11:30 p.m. reported shots fired in the area of Fifth and North Madison streets, police said. Responding officer found evidence of a shooting, but did not find anyone injured there.

Within minutes, however, police were notified that a 23-year-old man arrived at Wilmington Hospital's by private vehicle, seeking care for a gunshot wound. Shot in the upper torso, the man was stabilized there before he was taken to Christiana Hospital, police said.

He was admitted in critical condition.

headline: Man, 60, shot in head
formatted_address: 1200 block of Vandever Ave., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 60-year-old man was shot in the head while on Vandever Avenue Saturday afternoon, police said.

Officers were called about 3:20 p.m. to the 1200 block of Vandever Ave. for a report of a shooting, police said. Upon arrival, a man was found with a gunshot wound to the head.

He was treated on scene by New Castle County Paramedics before he was rushed to Christiana Hospital, where he was described in stable condition, police said.

headline: Man shot in chest near community center
formatted_address: 600 block of W. 6th St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A 24-year-old man was shot in the chest near Helen Chambers Park on West Sixth Street, police said.

The shooting was reported about 8:10 p.m. As police responded, officers found a vehicle in the 700 block of N. Jefferson St. which appeared to be transporting a shooting victim to the hospital, police said.

Police proceeded to escort the vehicle to Wilmington Hospital, where an injured man was removed from the vehicle with a gunshot wound to the chest, police said. Medics were able to stabilize the man before transporting him to Christiana Hospital, where he was admitted in critical condition.

headline: Man,22, shot in arm
formatted_address: Lamotte and Gordon streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 22-year-old man was shot in the arm Tuesday in Wilmington, police said.

Officers responding to reports of shots fired in the area of Gordon and Lamotte streets shortly before noon found evidence of a shooting but no one injured, police said.

Minutes later, however, staff at Wilmington Hospital alerted police that a man arrived at the hospital seeking treatment for a gunshot wound to the right arm. The victim was described as stable, police said.

headline: Three men shot, one fatally
formatted_address: 2500 block of N. Market St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 20-year-old Wilmington man was killed Thursday, and two others were injured in related incidents, police said. 

Just before 9 p.m., police were called to the 2500 block of N. Market St. to investigate a shots-fired complaint, police said. Upon arrival, officers found a 23-year-old man with gunshot wounds to his left arm and buttocks, police said, adding he he was target of a robbery. 

About two minutes later, police were notified of a second shooting victim inside of a vehicle at West 24th and North Madison streets. Police found Shaiquen Brown with gunshot wounds to his head and torso. He was taken to Christiana Hospital, where he died. 

As police were securing the two scenes, officers were notified by Wilmington Hospital Emergency Room staff that an 18-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his left shoulder had arrived by private vehicle, police said. Police have since identified him as Raquan Stevens of Wilmington.

headline: Man arrives at hospital after shots fired
formatted_address: Unit block of E. 24th St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Wilmington police responded to a complaint of shots fired Saturday on the first block of East 24th Street, but found no victims at the scene.

Shortly after the 6:45 p.m. complaint, a 48-year-old man arrived at Wilmington Hospital with a a gunshot wound to his left upper leg, according to the Wilmington Police Department.

headline: Man fatally shot in West Center City
formatted_address: 600 block of W. 6th St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A police unit on patrol heard the shots fired in the 600 block of W. Sixth St. about 1:45 p.m. Monday. 

A responding officer found a man at a residence in the middle of the block, suffering from a gunshot wound to his upper torso. 

The victim was treated on the scene by New Castle County Paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital, where 25-year-old Hassan Brown was later pronounced dead, police said.

headline: Woman grazed in shooting
formatted_address: 700 block of W. Seventh St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A woman was grazed in a shooting incident Saturday, police said.

Officers were dispatched about 10:10 p.m. after a caller reported shots fired in the area of Seventh and Monroe streets, police said. As they arrived, police were directed by people in the area to a home in the 700 block of W. Seventh St., police said.

Inside the home, they found a 33-year-old woman suffering from a minor graze wound or abrasion to her left foot, police said. The injured woman was taken by ambulance to St. Francis Hospital in Wilmington, where she was in good condition.

headline: Teen shot on East Side
address: E. Ninth and N. Pine streets
formatted_address: E. Ninth and N. Pine streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
An 18-year-old man was injured in a shooting in the city's East Side neighborhood. 

The shooting was reported shortly after 2:45 p.m. in the area of East Ninth and North Pine streets, and multiple units, including medics, were dispatched to the scene, police said.

Upon arrival, officers found the teenager with gunshot wounds to his torso and cheek, police said.

He was treated on scene by New Castle County Paramedics before he was taken to Christiana Hospital. 

Michael O. Newton, 35, has been charged with this shooting.

headline: Man shot a block from city police station
formatted_address: 400 block of E. Fourth St.
summary:
A 24-year-old man was shot in the leg just before midnight on Thursday near the intersection of Fourth and Lombard streets in Wilmington, according to city police.

Two officers on patrol from the community policing unit called in possible shots fired around the 400 block of E. Fourth St. at about 11:40 p.m. Just after calling it in, they found the victim, who had been shot in the upper left leg, according to police.

The victim was treated on the scene by New Castle County Paramedics and was taken to Christiana Hospital in stable condition, according to police.

headline: Teen shot in leg shows up at hospital
formatted_address: 200 block of W. 20th St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A  17-year-old boy showed up at the Wilmington Hospital with a gunshot wound to the leg, police said.

The teen arrived about 8:15 p.m. with a gunshot wound to his left thigh and said he was shot while in the 200 block of W. 20th St., though police were unable to locate a shooting scene and received no calls about shots fired.

headline: Saturday night shooting injures one
formatted_address: 23rd and Lamotte streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A man was in critical condition after being shot in his legs in Wilmington Saturday, police said. 

The shooting occurred about 11:15 p.m. near the intersection of 23rd and Lamotte streets. 

The 34-year-old victim was taken to Christiana Hospital, police said.

headline: Police shot man in wheelchair
formatted_address: S. Scott and Tulip streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police fatally shot a 28-year-old man in a wheelchair Wednesday at Tulip and South Scott streets. 

Police said officers responded to a 911 call at 3 p.m. about a man with a self-inflicted gunshot wound who was armed in the 1800 block of Lancaster Avenue. When officers arrived, they located the Jeremy “Bam” McDole in the 1800 block of Tulip Street, where they repeatedly told him to put down his weapon and raise his arms.

McDole did not comply and reached for his waistband for a handgun, police said. When McDole began to remove the gun, four officers opened fire. Police said officers found a .38 caliber gun at McDole’s side.

The family is disputing what police are saying.

headline: Man shot twice near Riverside community
formatted_address: First block of Jensen Drive, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A man was shot twice along Jensen Drive late Thursday morning, police said.

Officers were called about 11:00 a.m. to the first block of Jensen Drive for a possible shooting, but no victim was located, police said. About a half hour later, a 22-year-old man was found at the Knights Inn along Del. 9 in New Castle with a gunshot wound to his chest and a superficial wound to his jaw area.

He was treated on scene by New Castle County Paramedics and transported to Christiana Hospital, where he was described as stable.

headline: Crowd forms after man shot in chest
formatted_address: 600 block of N. Jefferson St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A man was shot in the chest and a large crowd growing disorderly and throwing rocks and bottles at officers, police said. 

Several officers were hit by thrown objects, but none required hospitalization, police said. 

The shooting was reported at 4:30 p.m. in the 600 block of Jefferson St., emergency dispatch officials said. The 23-year-old man was suffering from gunshot wounds to his upper torso  and lower extremity areas, police said. 

The injured man was taken by ambulance to Christiana Hospital, according to police.

headline: Man shot in leg
formatted_address: 2400 block of Northeast Blvd., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Police are investigating a shooting they said left a man with an injured leg.

Police received no reports of the shooting from 911 callers or alerts from the ShotSpotter surveillance system. But at 8:16 p.m. Saturday, police said, police were called to the emergency room of Wilmington Hospital, where an 18-year-old man had arrived for treatment of a gunshot wound to his left leg.

Preliminary investigation indicated the incident occurred in the area of the 2400 block of Northeast Blvd., police said. But investigators did not find evidence of the shooting there.

headline: Man was shot in the abdomen
formatted_address: First block of E. 23rd St, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A man was shot in the abdomen early Thursday, police said.

About 1:35 a.m., police responded to a report of a shooting in the first block of E. 23rd St., where they found the injured 23-year-old.

Investigating officers found no evidence of the shooting scene in the area where the man was found, police said, but the shooting remains under investigation.

headline: Teen shot in leg
formatted_address: West 28th and North West streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A report of a shooting came in about 8:40 p.m. in the area of West 28th and Washington streets, police said. Officers later located a scene at the intersection of West 28th and North West streets.

A 19-year-old man was located after dispatchers received a call for a man with a gunshot wound in the 200 block of West 27th Street.

The teen was shot in the right calf and treated on scene by New Castle County Paramedics before he was taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Gunfire penetrates house, hits man
formatted_address: 300 block of E. 14th St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A bullet went through a house and hit a man in the neck Monday morning, police said.

A caller reported shots fired about 12:35 a.m. in the 300 block of E. 14th St., police said. Responding officers found property damage on the block, but did not immediately find anyone injured.

People at the scene directed officers to a home on the block, where they found an 18-year-old man with a gunshot wound to the neck, police said.

New Castle County paramedics treated him at the scene before he was taken to Christiana Hospital,  police said. His condition was not available.

headline: 60-year-old man shot
formatted_address: N. Tatnall and W. 27th streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Wilmington police were investigating the shooting of a 73-year-old man in the 2700 block of N. Tatnall Street.

Officers were called to the 2700 block of Tatnall St. for shots fired about 4 p.m., police said. 

Officers found a shooting scene in the 100 block of W. 27th St., but redirected by residents to the 2700 block of N. Tatnall St. where they found a man with a graze wound to one of his legs, she said.

headline: 6-year-old girl shot in knee
formatted_address: 800 block of Bennett St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Gunfire struck a 6-year-old girl in the 800 block of Bennett St. in Wilmington around 6:30 p.m. Monday, Wilmington Police said.

The girl was treated on the scene and taken to the Wilmington Hospital Emergency Room, where she is in stable condition, police said.

Korie D. Henry, 31, of New Castle, has been charged with the shooting.

headline: Man shot in leg
formatted_address: West 27th and Enterprise streets,  Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Wilmington police were on the scene of a shooting at West 27th and Enterprise streets Thursday. 

A man, whose age was not immediately available, was shot in the leg, police said.

Multiple units were on scene and detectives had the block closed for investigation purposes. Further details from police were not immediately available.

headline: Man found shot dies
formatted_address: Fourth and Monroe streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A uniform officer notified city police just after 4 p.m. Wednesday of shots fired in the area of Fourth and Monroe streets, police said.

As police responded to that area, they found the man, who was shot in the abdomen, down in the 300 block of N. Monroe St. The victim was taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was pronounced dead, police said.

Police declined to release the victim's identity.

headline: Three men shot, one arrested
formatted_address: Fourth and Monroe streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Three men were shot Wednesday near the scene of an earlier shooting. 

Police said that one of three people injured was a suspect in the shooting, which occurred about 4:20 p.m. in the area of Fourth and Monroe streets.

Arriving officers found a 61-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his upper leg, police said. County paramedics treated him before he was taken to Christiana Hospital.

The two other injured men – including a suspect – were taken to hospitals by private vehicles, police said. Both were 24-year-olds with gunshot wounds of the upper legs, not considered to be life-threatening.

headline: Man repeatedly shot
formatted_address: 2700 block of Claymont St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A man was critically wounded after being repeatedly shot late Wednesday, police said.

The shooting was reported at 11:08 p.m. in the 2700 block of Claymont Street, police said. Responding officers found a 26-year-old man down with multiple gunshot wounds to the upper torso.

New Castle County paramedics treated him at the scene before he was taken to Christiana Hospital, police said.

headline: Man killed in Browntown neighborhood
formatted_address: Lower Oak and Marshall streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 22-year-old man was shot to death late Tuesday, police said. 

Police responded to a 911 call reporting a man down near Lower Oak and Marshall streets, police said.

Officers found the man in the 100 block of Lower Oak St., where New Castle County paramedics pronounced him dead at the scene. No information was disclosed the victim's gunshot wound. 

Police identified the victim as Quadrice Barksdale.

headline: Victim flags down police
formatted_address: 800 block of Spruce St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A man shot Wednesday flagged down officers responding to a report of his shooting, police.

The ShotSpotter surveillance system alerted police about 10:35 p.m. to shots fired in the 800 block of Spruce St. The injured man flagged down the responding officers as they arrived near Eighth and Pine streets, police said.

The 28-year-old man was shot in the hand.

headline: Three shot on Vandever Avenue
formatted_address: 800 block of Vandever Ave., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Three people were shot in what neighbors are calling a serious shooting at Vandever Avenue near North Church Street.

Police responded just after 7:30 p.m. to the 800 block of Vandever Ave. to a report of a shooting. Police found three injured men, who were taken to Christiana Hospital. 

A 29-year-old man and a 27-year-old man had each been shot in the left hip and buttocks area, according to police, and the third victim, a 20-year-old man, was about a block away on Vandever Avenue suffering from gunshot wounds to his left arm and leg.

headline: Shooting injures two men
formatted_address: 1300 block of Lancaster Ave., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Two men were shot early Tuesday near Lancaster Avenue and Franklin Street. 

Officers responded to a call a few blocks away, near Delamore Place and Lancaster Avenue, and found a 40-year-old man with an abdominal gunshot wound at about 1:10 a.m. Shortly after that, police were notified that a 19-year-old man had arrived at the St. Francis Hospital with a gunshot wound to his right wrist.

Both men were wounded in the same incident on the 1300 block of Lancaster Avenue, according to police, who expect to release more information later on Tuesday.

Police later said the 19-year-old man was the accomplice of a 17-year-old shooter.

headline: One injured in Canby Park shooting
formatted_address: 1800 block of Prospect Road, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police were called out to a shooting at Canby Park found a 37-year-old man suffering from a gunshot wound to his abdominal area. 

The man was treated by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was described as in stable condition. 

The circumstances surrounding the shooting were under investigation.

headline: Man, 25, shot in ankle
formatted_address: Jensen Drive
summary:
A 25-year-old man showed up at Wilmington Hospital after being shot shortly before midnight on Thursday, according to Wilmington Police.

At about 11:45 p.m. police were notified that the man had arrived at the hospital in a personal vehicle with a gunshot wound in his left ankle.

headline: Two shot in Wilmington's East Side
formatted_address: E. 10th and Bennett streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A woman was shot in the cheek and a man shot in the arm on Wilmington's East Side Sunday evening.

Police responded to the 700 block of E. 10th St. on a report of a shooting called in about 6:15 p.m. Arriving officers found a 46-year-old woman in the 900 block of Spruce St. with a gunshot wound to the cheek area, and a 42-year-old man in the 1000 block of Spruce Street with a gunshot wound to the arm.

Both victims were taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Two, including a 13-year-old, shot in Hilltop
formatted_address: N. Harrison and Conrad streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police were called out to Third and North Harrison street on a report of a shooting about 4:40 p.m. 

Arriving officers founts two victims: a 13-year-old girl who was suffering from a gunshot wound to her leg; and a 23-year-old man suffering from a gunshot wound to his right hip area. 

Both victims were treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics before being taken to Christiana Emergency Room and the Nemours/Alfred I. duPont Hospital for Children. Both were in good condition, police said.

headline: Man critically wounded in East Side shooting
formatted_address: Taylor and Kirkwood streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Wilmington police detectives were on foot in the area of the Ninth and Spruce streets when they called in shots being fired in the immediate area about 5:10 p.m. 

The detectives found a 27-year-old man wounded near the corner of Taylor and Kirkwood Streets. He was suffering from gunshot wounds to his torso and lower extremity areas. 

The victim was treated by New Castle County paramedics and taken by state police helicopter to Christiana Hospital, where he was described to be in critical condition.

headline: Shooting in Southbridge
formatted_address: S. Heald and Lobdell streets, Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A shooting in Wilmington's Southbridge neighborhood left a man in the hospital and a white Honda riddled with at least 21 bullet holes.

The shooting happened just before 10:30 p.m. Monday on Lobdell Street, east of South Heald Street, and outside of the Casbar Lounge. 

Police did not find a victim at the scene, but were notified of a 22-year-old man who arrived at Wilmington Hospital with gunshot wounds to the left forearm and lower left leg. The victim is in stable condition.

headline: Teen shoot in the back
address: Maryland Ave. and S. Harrison St.
formatted_address: Maryland Ave. and S. Harrison St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 17-year-old boy was critically injured Tuesday afternoon near Pulaski Park after he was shot in the back, police said.

At least two dozen officers were on the scene at the intersection of Maryland Avenue and South Harrison Street at about 2:30 p.m. Tuesday. Upon arrival, officers found a teen with a gunshot wound to the back.

He was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was listed in critical condition, police said.

headline: Shooting injures 19-year-old man
formatted_address: N. West and W. 20th streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 19-year-old man was shot in the torso on 20th Street near West Street, police said. 

The man was walking up 20th Street about 7 p.m. when five shots rang out, police said. He went into a house where people had been out on the porch and waited there until police arrived.

He was in stable condition when he was taken by ambulance to Christiana Hospital

Police couldn't find where the shooting occurred because there were no bullet casings on the ground.

headline: Man shot in hand
formatted_address: 2500 block of Carter St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers responded to the 2500 block of Carter St. at about 5:55 p.m. for a report of shots fired, police said 

Although a shooting scene was located nearby, police said no victim was found upon arrival. 

About two hours, officers were called to Christiana Hospital about a man suffering from a gunshot wound to the right hand, police said. He was treated for his injuries and released.

headline: Man shot multiple times
formatted_address: 200 block of W. 30th St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Officers called to the 200 block of W. 30th Street for a shooting, found a 28-year-old man in his vehicle suffering from multiple gunshot wounds, police said. 

He was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics before being taken to Christiana Hospital.

Police did not release his condition.

headline: Boy, 15, shot in arm
formatted_address: 2700 block of Northeast Blvd., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Wilmington police were investigating a shooting that left a 15-year-old boy injured in the 2700 block of Northeast Blvd. Saturday night.

Reports of a shooting and a possible person down in the street came in shortly after 10:30 p.m. Saturday, according to police scanner reports. Officers arriving at the reported location – also known as Governor Printz Boulevard – did not find a victim or shooting scene. 

About 20 minutes later, however, officers were contacted by Wilmington Hospital staff that a teen boy had arrived with a gunshot would to his right bicep.

headline: Wilmington man fatally shot in head
formatted_address: 700 block of E. 22nd St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 30-year-old Wilmington man who was found with a gunshot wound to his head has died.

Jabari Saunders died late Tuesday from a gunshot injury he received earlier that day, said police. 

Saunders was found about 1:30 p.m. in the 700 block of E. 22nd St. by Wilmington police responding to a report of shots fired. Saunders was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics before he was taken to Chrsitana Hospital, where he died, police said.

headline: Boy, 16, shot in leg
formatted_address: 2500 block of Bowers St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 16-year-old walking in the 2500 block of Bowers St. in Wilmington was shot in the leg.

Officers were called to the block at about 9:45 p.m. for a report of shots fired, but police could not find a shooting victim or scene in the area. 

Shortly after the report, a 16-year-old boy arrived at Wilmington Hospital with a gunshot wound to his upper right leg, police said.

headline: Man shot in leg found blocks from incident
formatted_address: 22nd and Pine streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 26-year-old male was shot in the leg, police said.  

Officers responded to calls of shots fired in the area of 22nd and Pine streets, about 5:45 p.m. Wednesday. On the way, police found a victim with a gunshot wound to the left leg at 18th and Market streets. 

The man was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital. 

A preliminary investigation found the shooting occurred in the 2200 block of N. Market St.

headline: Boy, 15, shot in thigh
formatted_address: 1300 block of Read St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 15-year-old boy was treated for a gunshot wound after Wilmington police found the injured teen in the city's Hedgeville neighborhood.

Officers were called about 10:15 p.m. in reference to a shooting in the 1300 block of Read St. Arriving officers found the youth suffering from a gunshot wound to his left thigh area, said Sgt. Andrea Janvier, a Wilmington police spokeswoman.

The victim was treated by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was reported to be stable.

headline: Man, 27, shot in hand
address: N. Monroe Street and Concord Avenue,
formatted_address: North Monroe Street and Concord Avenue, Wilmington, De 19802
summary:
Wilmington police showed up at the intersection of N. Monroe Street and Concord Avenue for a complaint that shots had been fired, but they found no victim. 

That was at about 6:30 p.m. and, minutes later, police found out that a 27-year-old man had gone to Wilmington Hospital's emergency room with a gunshot wound to his hand.

headline: Teen arrested in shooting
formatted_address: 23rd and Locust streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Wilmington police charged a teen boy with shooting a 21-year-old man in the area of 23rd and Locust streets.

The 15-year-old boy, whose name was not released by police, was charged with assault, possession of a firearm during the commission of a felony and possession of a weapon by a prohibited juvenile person.

Police responding to calls of a shooting were directed a few blocks away to the 2300 block of Jessup St. where they found a 21-year-old man with a graze wound to his back.

headline: Man shot inside gas station
formatted_address: 1001 W. 4th St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Officers were patrolling the area of Third and North Jackson streets when they heard gunfire. 

Officers then saw a man running east on Fourth Street and continue south onto Adams Street. When officers intercepted him, police learned the 24-year-old man was suffering from a gun shot wound to the upper left arm. 

At this point, police learned the suspect, 35-year-old Michael Newton, of Newark, was inside the Liberty Gas Station, where the shooting took place. Newton was arrested and police recovered a 25-caliber handgun.

headline: Man dies after being shot
formatted_address: unit block of E. 23rd St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 36-year-old man, who was fatally shot, was identified as Antoine Perkins of Wilmington, police said.

Police arrived at the unit block of East 22nd Street shortly before 4:30 p.m. Monday to find Perkins with a gunshot wound to his head. He was taken to Christiana Hospital, where he died.

headline: Man shot in stomach
formatted_address: 600 block of S. Harrison St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 35-year-old man was shot in the stomach Wednesday night in Wilmington's Hedgeville neighborhood. 

Officers responded to the 600 block of S. Harrison St. for a report of shots fired, but found no one. 

Police were later notified that a 35-year-old man had arrived at Wilmington Hospital with a gunshot wound to the stomach. He arrived by private vehicle.

headline: Two injured in Hilltop shooting
address: W. Third and N. Broom streets
formatted_address: W. Third and N. Broom streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police responded to a shooting in Wilmington’s Hilltop neighborhood that left a 17-year-old with a gunshot wound to his leg.

Arriving officers found the wounded teen in the 200 block of N. Broom St. He was treated on scene by New Castle  County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital in good condition. 

While on the scene, police were notified of a second victim, a 35-year-old man, who had been grazed by a bullet. He is in good condition, according to a statement from the Wilmington police.

headline: Two men shot, one fatally
formatted_address: East 23rd and Lamotte streets, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Two men were shot, one fatally, near the site of another killing last week.  

The gunfire erupted shortly before 10 p.m. near the corner of East 23rd and Lamotte streets. Arriving officer were directed to the 300 block of E. 23rd St., where they found a 25-year-old man with a gunshot wound to the head. He was taken to Christiana Hospital where he was pronounced dead.

Another victim was located at Concord Avenue and N. Market Street with a bullet wound to his left arm. The 27-year-old was taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was reported to be stable.

headline: Man, 38, shot in torso and hip
formatted_address: Concord Avenue and Jefferson Street, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 38-year-old man was shot about 7:20 p.m., police said. 

Officers responded to a report of shots fired in the area of Concord Avenue and Jefferson Street and found a shooting scene but no victim. Minutes later, police were notified about a man with gunshot wounds had arrived at Wilmington Hospital by private vehicle. 

The man was shot in his upper torso and right hip.

headline: Teen first shooting victim of 2016
formatted_address: 600 block of W. Fifth St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
Police are investigating a shooting that left an 18-year-old man critically injured near the William "Hicks" Anderson Community Center in West Center City.

Police were called about 1:30 p.m. to the 600 block of West Fifth St. for a report of a shooting. Arriving officers found a the victim with a gunshot wound on the left side of his upper torso. 

He was treated at the scene before he was taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was admitted in critical conditions.

headline: Five shot, one fatally, in home invasion
formatted_address: 900 block of Brown St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A home invasion in the Browntown area left one man dead and four others injured, police said.

Officers were dispatched to a house in the 900 block of Brown Street for a report that two people had been shot, a 28-year-old man and a 51-year-old woman. The victims were taken to Christiana Hospital, where the man, who was shot in the leg, was reported as stable. The woman,  who was shot in the stomach, was in critical condition. 

Another set of victims drove themselves to St. Francis Hospital. A 49-year-old man, who was shot in his left hand and abdomen, was described as being in serious condition but stable, while a 21-year-old man, with gunshot wounds to his shoulder, leg and abdomen, was listed in critical condition. Both were later taken to Christiana Hospital.

Police learned of a fifth victim, 20-year-old Ira Brown, who had several gunshot wounds to his lower extremities. He arrived at the Wilmington Hospital in a personal vehicle and transported to Christiana Hospital where he died, police said.

headline: Man, 41, shot in buttocks
formatted_address: 1800 block of W. Second St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 41-year-old man was shot in the buttocks along West Second Street by two unknown people, police said.

The man arrived at St. Francis Hospital about 9:15 p.m. in a private vehicle, police said. He told police he was shot while in the 1800 block of W. Second St., by two men who demanded his property.

A struggle ensued between the three men during which the 41-year-old was shot by the armed robber.

headline: Man, 28, shot dead
formatted_address: 1200 block of N. Locust St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A 28-year-old man died after being shot, police said.

Officers responded to a report of a person down at a garage in the 1200 block of N. Locust St. about 6:30 p.m., police said. They found the man with apparent gunshot wounds to his upper torso, police said.

The man was treated by New Castle County paramedics before being transported to Christiana Hospital, where Therman Redden was pronounced dead, police said.

A 50-year-old man was shot as two men tried to rob him.

Officers were called to the 600 block of E. 22nd St. for a report of a shooting about 6:30 p.m.,  police said.

There, they found a man with a gunshot wound to his upper right leg. The victim was treated by New Castle County paramedics before he was taken to Christiana Hospital in good condition, police said.

The man told police that he was walking in the 2200 block of Jessup St. when two men tried to rob him. During the struggle, the man was shot in the leg, police said.

She was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital in stable condition.

He was treated by New Castle County Paramedics before he was transported to Christiana Hospital, Janvier said. He was admitted and described as stable, she said.

Minutes later, officers were notified that a shooting victim had arrived by personal vehicle at Wilmington Hospital suffering from a gunshot wound to his left foot. The victim was reported to be in good condition.

He was treated by New Castle County paramedics on scene for an apparent gunshot wound to the upper torso before he was transported to Christiana Hospital. He was later pronounced dead.

formatted_address: 2100 block of N. Pine St., Wilmington, DE 19802

The victim was treated on the scene by New Castle County paramedics and later taken to the Christiana Hospital, police said. The victim is listed in critical condition.

Police found the victim who was grazed in his right knee. He was treated at the scene and taken to Wilmington Hospital in good condition, an official said. No motive or suspect information was provided by police.

Kevron Willimas, 22, of Wilmington, has been charged in the shooting.

headline: Man, 22, shot dead

formatted_address: W. Seventh and N. Harrison streets, Wilmington, DE 19805

Copeland was suffering from gunshot wounds to his upper torso, police said. He was pronounced dead at the scene.

headline: Man killed near Tilton Park
formatted_address: Seventh and Franklin streets, Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Wilmington police are investigating the second deadly shooting in less than a week in the quiet neighborhood near Tilton Park.

On Monday night at 6:45 p.m., police responded to the area near Seventh and Franklin streets for a report of several shots fired and found a 23-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his back.

The man, Leroy Collins, was treated on the scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital, where he was pronounced dead shortly after arrival.

headline: Man shot near Market Street dies

Officers responding to a complaint of a person down found a 27-year-old man suffering from a gunshot wound to his upper torso, said Sgt. Andrea Janvier, a Wilmington police said. The victim was unresponsive. The victim was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital where he died shortly after arriving, Janvier said.

Upon arrival, the officers were directed to a house on the block where they found a 26-year-old man with a gunshot wound to the upper-right leg, police said. The man was treated on the scene and taken to the Christiana Hospital, where he was reported to be stable.

About 9:20 p.m. Monday, police officers were flagged down outside the St. Francis Hospital in reference to a shooting victim. The unidentified man had been driven to the hospital by personal vehicle, police said. Arriving officers learned the man was suffering from a gunshot. 

The shooting was believed to have occurred in the area of 11th Street and Clifford Brown Walk, but officers who went to the area did not locate a shooting scene.

headline: Man, 19, critically wounded

He was taken to Christiana Hospital and was reported to be stable, police said.

headline: Man accidentally shoots father
formatted_address: 800 block of Morrow St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A 25-year-old man was arrested after police said he accidentally shot his father in the foot.

Police were called to the Wilmington Hospital about 9:35 a.m. in reference to a 51-year-old man with a gunshot wound to his right foot.

Investigators with the Criminal Investigations Division determined the shooting was accidental after it was explained that David Avant was showing his father a gun in a home on the 800 block of Morrow St., police said. The gun was accidentally fired, hitting the father in the foot.

Avant surrendered to police Wednesday. His father has been released from the hospital.

headline: Teen shot in ankle

A 17-year-old boy was shot in the ankle, police said. 

City police were called to the 200 block of Franklin St. in reference to a shots fire complaint. Arriving officers found a teen boy suffering from a gunshot wound to the left  ankle. 

The boy was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital.

headline: 22-year-old man shot dead
formatted_address: 200 block of N. Connell St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Police identified the victim of a fatal shooting in the Hilltop neighborhood as Christian Serrano.

On Thursday Wilmington police were in the 200 block of N. Connell St. investigating the shooting of 22-year-old Serrano, of Wilmington. 

Police gave little more information, other than to say the shooting occurred about 6:30 p.m.

Jose Mareta, 19 of New Castle, and Joshua Gonzalez, 17 of Wilmington, were charged with the killing.

headline: 15-year-old shoots himself in chest
formatted_address: 300 block of New Castle Ave., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A 15-year-old boy playing with a gun accidentally shot himself in the chest, police said. 

According to police, the boy retrieved a handgun from inside of his residence in the 300 block of New Castle Ave., then went into the backyard and began spinning with it. That's when he shot himself in the chest, police said. 

A 911 call was received from within the residence alerting police to the shooting, but when officers arrived the victim had already been taken to the Wilmington Hospital by private vehicle. He was later taken to Christiana Hospital where he was listed in critical condition.

headline: Woman shot in West Center City

A 21-year-old woman was shot in Wilmington's West Center City neighborhood.

The shooting was reported about 1:10 p.m. in the 600 block of N. Jefferson St. 

Arriving officers found a shooting scene but no victim, police said. Minutes later, a woman arrived at Wilmington Hospital in a private vehicle with a gunshot wound to her right arm.

headline: Man, 42, shot in knee
formatted_address: 400 block of Porter St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 42-year-old man was shot in the right knee while in the 400 block of Porter St., police said.

Officers were called about 11:40 p.m. to the area for a report of a shooting . Arriving officers found the man suffering from the gunshot wound to the knee. 

New Castle County paramedics treated the man on scene before he was transported to Christiana Hospital, police said.

headline: Man shot in elbow
formatted_address: 12th Street and Northeast Boulevard, Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
A man was shot in the elbow while walking in the area of 12th Street and Northeast Boulevard, police said.

Shortly after midnight Monday, a man arrived by private vehicle at Wilmington Hospital with a gunshot wound to the elbow, police said. His age was not released. 

The man told officers he was walking when he felt a sharp pain in his elbow area. After he was stabilized, the man was transported to Christiana Hospital.

headline: Two shot Easter Sunday
formatted_address: 2700 block of N. Pine St., Wilmington, DE 19802
summary:
Two people were injured in a shooting Sunday night along Pine Street, according to police.

Officers were called about 7:45 p.m. to the 2700 block of N. Pine St., for a report of multiple shots fired. Upon arrival, they found a shooting scene where casings littered the intersection.

As police investigated, a person with a gunshot wound to the leg arrived arrived at Wilmington Hospital in a personal vehicle, police said. Shortly after 8 p.m., a second victim was located in the area of 28th and Market streets, police said. That person also had a gunshot wound to the leg, police said.

Both shooting victims were described in good condition.

headline: Man fatally shot on Elm Street
formatted_address: 1100 block of Elm St., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
A 40-year-old man was fatally shot in the 1100 block of Elm St., police said.

Police were alerted of a shooting about 9:30 p.m. by ShotSpotter, a system that uses sound sensors to find the origin of a gunshot within a few feet. Arriving officers found a victim on the sidewalk with multiple gunshot wounds to the upper torso, police said.

New Castle County paramedics transported Jason C. Hicks to Christiana Hospital, where he was pronounced dead at about 10:15 p.m., police said.

headline: Man goes to hospital day after being shot
formatted_address: 400 block of Maryland Ave., Wilmington, DE 19805
summary:
Nearly a day after Wilmington police responded to a shooting in the 400 block of Maryland Ave., a 28-year-old man with a gunshot wound showed up at Christiana Hospital Tuesday.

Officers were notified about 2:20 p.m. Tuesday that a man with a gunshot wound to the left lower leg came to the hospital, police said. Through further investigation, police identified him as a victim of what police had formerly classified as a shots fired incident Monday along Maryland Avenue.

Witnesses on the scene reported that a man was down on the sidewalk but then got up and left the scene.

headline: Teen shot after pointing gun at police
formatted_address: 400 block of W. Third St., Wilmington, DE 19801
summary:
A Wilmington officer shot a 17-year-old boy in the right knee after the teen pointed a replica handgun at an officer, police said.

The incident began about 6:45 p.m. when police were called to respond to a gun complaint. Arriving officers saw the suspect at Second and N. West streets. When they tried to stop him, he fled and police chased him. Officers caught up to him in the 400 block of W. Third St. where he tripped and fell. 

When he got up, police said he pulled a gun from his waistband and pointed it at one of the officers. That's when an officer shot the teen in the right knee, police said. 

The teen was treated by New Castle County paramedics and taken to Christiana Hospital in good condition. The officer, a 10-year veteran of the department, has been placed on administrative duty, per department policy.

A Delaware Attorney General report clearing the police man in the shooting identified the officer as Master Cpl. Darriel Tynes and the teen as Taje Beasley.

headline: Man shot in upper torso

Police responded to the 3100 block of N. Madison St. about 8:50 p.m. in reference to a shooting. Arriving offices found a man suffering from a gunshot wound to his upper torso, police said. 

The man sat on the steps of a nearby residence and was assisted on the scene by police and New Castle County paramedics, who then took him to Christiana Hospital.

He was treated at the scene by New Castle County paramedics before he was transported to Christiana Hospital, police said.

headline: Man shot dead in Hilltop

The 34-year-old man, identified as Terrance Kinard, was treated on scene by New Castle County paramedics and taken to the Christiana Hospital, where he later died.

headline: Two shot on North Market Street
